Loop iter25 (2026-05-26): completed the wrapper-refresh fix the iter23 attempt got WRONG. iter23 added ensureWrapperInstalled() but called it only inside spawnPlugkitWatcher, which bootstrapPlugkit skips via early-return (line 745) when the binary is up-to-date AND a watcher is already running — exactly the gm-plugkit-only-JS-update case (no wasm bump). So the installed ~/.gm-tools wrapper stayed stale despite the fix. iter25 fix: moved ensureWrapperInstalled() to the UNCONDITIONAL bootstrap-start block next to ensureSkillMdCurrent (before any early return), so every session bootstrap sha-refreshes the installed wrapper. Validated: refreshed 06be66de->7724a21b, isBrowserRelevantPath grep 0->2. LESSON: a refresh/install step must live in the unconditional bootstrap prologue, not inside a spawn path that early-returns skip when the daemon is already up. This is the third version-transition-lifecycle finding (kill-stale, watcher-dies-on-publish, now wrapper-refresh-unreachable) — the common root is that bootstrap branches skip maintenance steps when the daemon is already running.